    "Benjamin Keach": "If my own old, or new personal and inherent righteousness, is joined with the merits of Christ, or through the virtue of his merits it justifies me, then I have room to boast: as the apostle speaks of Abraham `[char_Abraham_Exo_17]`, \u201cIf Abraham `[char_Abraham_Exo_17]` were justified by works, he had whereof to glory, but not before God,\u201d Rom. iv."
